 Cradock - The Family Violence, Child Protection and Sexual offences Unit in Cradock is urging the public to assist in finding two biological sisters, Sunick Ferreira, aged 12 years old, and Ashley Olivier, aged 5 years old. "They went missing on Friday after an arranged visit with their biological parents, Marius and Tasha Ferreira," said police spokesperson, Captain Lariane Jonker. "On above mentioned date the grandfather and legal gaurdian of the minors reported them missing. "It is alleged that the Ferreira couple shortly left after the children were dropped off at their home for an arranged visit by a social worker." She said that they left the premises with a travelling bag and the two children. "The children were dressed in a white and yellow dress, blue pants and pink shoes." Anyone with information is requested to contact the Investigation Officer Detective Constable Sibongile Ngesi on cell phone: 0794145565. Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 